do you think this is a good analogy i work at mcdonalds and for the whole day the most important thing in the world is cooking cleaning and assembling as quickly and efficiently as possible but i also have fun and muck around with the other guys there which makes me feel good about myself when i go home i find that i remember the fun we had but the stress of doing the job seems useless now if i said that mcdonalds is like life finishing for the day is like death doing my work is like having an education career and having a laugh is my emotional spiritual side does it seem that the emphasis on our careers is folly i think this is what plato was getting at when he wrote the timaeus and critias the fact that you know about timaeus and critias i give you kudo points i think thats a great analogy in retrospect you may have changed the way i look at people who work at mcdonalds my phiosophy for life is to never take anything for granted because it can be gone as quickly as it came Waking the Dragons Plato Timaeus (dialogue) Socrates Deluge (mythology) Critias (dialogue) Philo Reincarnation Atlantis Social rule Soul A Course In Miracles Republic (dialogue) Ancient Greek literature Justification (theology) Platonic solid Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis Stoicism Religion The Ashlee Simpson Show Apology (Plato) Timaeus (historian) Avenue Q Nicomachean Ethics Ye Shengtao Aristotle Atomism Essentialism Diablo II: Lord of Destruction Holiness movement Friedrich Schleiermacher Art 3rd Rock from the Sun Satanism Undergrads Intelligent design EastEnders Clement of Alexandria Dry cleaning Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Pitaten Past teachings of Prem Rawat Epistemology Ex-gay The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie RuneScape skills Spidey Super Stories Upholstery Goodness and value theory Force (Star Wars) Bon Jovi Transactional analysis Maimonides Criticisms of Charismatic and Pentecostal belief Acts of the Apostles About a Boy Lucid dreaming 2000 Australian Grand Prix Internet s